wiki.content:
"Stronger" is the third single from pop singer Britney Spears released from the album Oops!... I Did It Again during the fourth quarter of 2000.
 
 The song was written and produced by frequent collaborators Max Martin and Rami in 1999. In this song, Spears sings about overcoming the difficulties of love as she proclaims she is "stronger than yesterday". There is an allusion to "...Baby One More Time": "...my loneliness ain't killing me no more".
